SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [flag . . .] file -lform -locurses [library . . .]

       #include <form.h>

       FORM *new_form(FIELD **fields); int free_form(FORM *form);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       new_form creates a new form connected  to  the  designated
       fields and returns a pointer to the form.

       free_form  disconnects  the form from its associated field
       pointer array and deallocates the space for the form.

 vvaalluuee
       new_form always returns NULL on error.  free_form  returns
       one of the following:
       ---------------------------------------------------------
       E_OK             -   The function returned successfully.
       E_BAD_ARGUMENT   -   An argument is incorrect.
       E_POSTED         -   The form is posted.

NNoottiicceess
       The  header  file form.h automatically includes the header
       files eti.h and ocurses.h.

